hooks.prompt:
Respond with ONLY a JSON object, nothing else.

Was this a significant code change (feature, architecture, refactor, deps) outside .engram/, tests, and docs?

If yes and no .engram/decisions/ file written yet this session: {"ok": true, "reason": "Consider recording this decision with @engram:capture."}
Otherwise: {"ok": true}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object, nothing else.

If the file path is NOT inside .engram/decisions/ or .engram/_private/: {"ok": true}

If it IS an engram signal file, validate: (1) starts with --- frontmatter, (2) has date: YYYY-MM-DD, (3) has tags: with at least one tag, (4) has # Title after frontmatter, (5) has a lead paragraph >= 20 chars explaining why.

All valid: {"ok": true}
Any invalid: {"ok": false, "reason": "what failed and how to fix it"}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object, nothing else.

Did this subagent make architectural recommendations or design decisions?

If yes: {"ok": true, "reason": "Subagent made recommendations — consider @engram:capture and @engram:query."}
If no: {"ok": true}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object, nothing else.

Are there decisions discussed in this conversation not yet recorded as .engram/decisions/ files?

If yes: {"ok": true, "reason": "Unrecorded decisions found — consider @engram:capture before compaction."}
If no: {"ok": true}

Always ok:true — never block compaction.

Respond with ONLY a JSON object, nothing else.

Might any .engram/decisions/ files benefit from enrichment (missing tags, body, or rationale)?

